Meat.description: Cattle meat, commonly referred to as beef, is a rich source of high-quality protein, essential vitamins, and minerals such as iron, zinc, and B vitamins. It is derived from cows, bulls, and steers, and offers a variety of cuts including steaks, roasts, and ground beef, each with its unique flavor and texture.

Goat meat, known as chevon or mutton (depending on the age of the goat), is a lean and flavorful protein source prized in many culinary traditions. It is rich in essential nutrients such as iron, potassium, and vitamin B12, while being lower in fat and cholesterol compared to other red meats.

Camel meat is a delicacy in many cultures, particularly in Middle Eastern, African, and Asian cuisines. Known for its tender texture and slightly sweet flavor, camel meat is a rich source of protein, iron, and vitamin B. It is lower in fat compared to beef and lamb, making it a healthier red meat alternative.

Sheep meat, commonly known as lamb or mutton depending on the age of the sheep, is a popular choice in many cuisines worldwide. It is prized for its tender texture and distinct flavor, which can range from mild and delicate in younger lambs to richer and more robust in mature sheep.
